headline: Humana raises annual profit forecast as medical costs stabilize
summary: The company said its strong quarterly performance was also driven by better-than-expected membership in individual Medicare Advantage plans and strength in its primary care segment CenterWell.  Larger competitor UnitedHealth flagged underestimation of medical costs on Tuesday, and also provided a full-year profit forecast that fell short of analysts' already diminished estimates.  Humana reported a quarterly medical cost ratio - the percentage of premiums spent on medical care - of 89.7%, up from 88.9% a year earlier, but in line with analysts' estimates of 89.71%.
